en.label:
In this survey, you’ll explore all of Qlarr’s question types—from quick text inputs to interactive rankings and media uploads.

Each section highlights when and why to use each type, so you can build smarter, more engaging surveys for anything from customer feedback to field research.

Let’s jump in and see how flexible your surveys can get!
Text-based questions are great for collecting open-ended input, precise details, and structured responses like numbers or email addresses.
Short Text - For quick, specific answers
en.description: What’s your go-to survey platform?

en.label: Long Text - For open feedback and deeper insights
en.description: What makes this platform your preferred choice?

en.label: Number - For exact values and quantifiable data
en.description: Roughly how many surveys have you created so far?

en.label: Email - For contact collection and follow-ups
en.description: Drop your email below!

en.label: For additional setup options for any question, click on the gear icon ⚙️ above the question on the right and select "Setup" from the menu on the left.
You’ve just seen how Qlarr handles clear inputs like text, numbers, and email. Now let’s see how it turns choices into quick and intuitive interactions.
